I_kwDOKzVPS86ZN0tg.body:
While working through some issues I noticed there are some caching optimizations pending, redundant calls being made and load time could improve. A clear example was that for each issue the organization's avatar was fetched, meaning that for 144 issues within 3 repos, where 3 calls could have been made we were making 144. This was solved at #106. 

Some code parts are also not respecting single responsibility principle, there are tries to set cache outside of a fetch function. This leads to resource waste and subsequently worse performance. 

For example, the following O(n) function where n is issues array length is being called 4 different times in different places:

```
export function applyAvatarsToIssues() {
  const container = taskManager.getContainer();
  const issueElements = Array.from(container.querySelectorAll(".issue-element-inner"));

  issueElements.forEach((issueElement) => {
    const orgName = issueElement.querySelector(".organization-name")?.textContent;
    if (orgName) {
      const avatarUrl = organizationImageCache.get(orgName);
      if (avatarUrl) {
        const avatarImg = issueElement.querySelector("img");
        if (avatarImg) {
          avatarImg.src = URL.createObjectURL(avatarUrl);
        }
      }
    }
  });
}
```

![image](https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/a0551a06-f3f4-4fb3-b8b0-4070b1b5e294)

The code base could benefit from general optimizations and a principle-based approach. I believe a 2-3 hour thorough review should be enough to identify, test and fix some of the problems.

