              @whilefoo maybe we could simplify to just `collaborator` and `contributor`, and then map a group of roles to these two? Admin would just have no limits. I can do that in a secondary pull-request. @0x4007 rfc

_Originally posted by @gentlementlegen in https://github.com/ubiquity-os-marketplace/command-start-stop/issues/116#issuecomment-2569982989_

To simplify the roles and avoid a long and complex configuration, we should regroup roles under `collaborator` (anyone with write access or from the organization) and `contributor` (everyone else). Admins should have no limits.

I_kwDOL-In886cAq7S.body:
              It is still weird to me that the user privacy affects a search because the profile is public. Can we consider using GQL with issues search instead of the search API? Something like
```gql
query($organization: String!, $author: String!) {
  organization(login: $organization) {
    repositories(first: 100) {
      nodes {
        issues(first: 100, states: OPEN, filterBy: {createdBy: $author}) {
          nodes {
            title
            url
            createdAt
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

with

```json
{
  "organization": "ubiquity",
  "author": "sshivaditya2019"
}
```

would achieve the same result. I don't know if that would resolve the issue but it's worth a try.

_Originally posted by @gentlementlegen in https://github.com/ubiquity/work.ubq.fi/issues/119#issuecomment-2440640493_

