I_kwDOJGfp8c5rGY7G.body:
There's a lot of abuse in our codebases with contributors using "!" 

Example: 
```typescript
let element: HTMLElement | null = document.getElementById('test');

// This would throw a TypeScript error without the "!" because element could be null
let value: string = element!.innerText;
```

Enforce that this can not pass our linters.

I_kwDOLUK0B87KLZ1_.body:
@whilefoo I think pagination will require switching from REST to GraphQL, because

- listCommits can only list 250 items, otherwise we have to use the commits API and filter ourselves to get them all
- `getCommit` has an open issue about the file pagination not working as expected since 2020

I can change this to GraphQL in a separate task.

_Originally posted by @gentlementlegen in https://github.com/ubiquity-os-marketplace/text-conversation-rewards/pull/420#discussion_r2328837512_


REST Api doesn't seem able to properly paginate results on these endpoints.

We should use
```
  const query = `
    query GetPullRequestCommits($owner: String!, $repo: String!, $pullNumber: Int!) {
      repository(owner: $owner, name: $repo) {
        pullRequest(number: $pullNumber) {
          commits(first: 100) {
            edges {
              node {
                commit {
                  oid
                  messageHeadline
                  author {
                    name
                    email
                  }
                  committedDate
                }
              }
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  `;
```

For the files pagination
```
  const query = `
    query($owner: String!, $repo: String!, $oid: GitObjectID!) {
      repository(owner: $owner, name: $repo) {
        object(oid: $oid) {
          ... on Commit {
            oid
            message
            author {
              name
              email
              date
            }
            committer {
              name
              email
              date
            }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  `;
```

